        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Bell's Palsy: facial muscle weakness (VII cranial nerve, peripheral)",
            "Guidelines on evaluation and management (Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg 149:656, 2013)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Etiologies"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Herpes simplex (HSV) (Types 1, 2) (most common)",
            "Others: Varicella zoster (VZV), HHV-6, Lyme disease"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Primary Regimens"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "As soon as possible after onset of palsy: Prednisone 1 mg/kg po divided bid x 5 days then taper to 5 mg bid over the next 5 days (total of 10 days prednisone) plus either:"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Acyclovir",
                "dose": "1600-2400 mg",
                "route": "po daily (divided q4h)",
                "frequency": "x 10 days"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Valacyclovir",
                "dose": "1000-1500 mg",
                "route": "po daily (divided bid or tid)",
                "frequency": "x 7 days"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Famciclovir",
                "dose": "750 mg",
                "route": "po daily",
                "frequency": "x 7 days"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Alternative Regimens"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Corticosteroids alone (not as effective as combination regimens above)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Comments"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Important to rule out Lyme disease in endemic areas; treatment is different (see Lyme disease).",
            "Systemic review, meta-analysis demonstrated clear benefit of combination steroids plus antiviral therapy (Laryngoscope 2021)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
